" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 502px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Immunoglobulin genes",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 482px; height: 195px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The &micro; and &delta; C genes are those nearest to the assembled VDJ sequence. Transcription of a complete immunoglobulin heavy-chain gene starts at the V sequence and proceeds through the &micro; and &delta; sequences before terminating. The mature B cell expresses both IgM and IgD, which are the only isotypes produced by B lymphocytes prior to contact with antigen.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
